Members of the National Assembly of Wales fear to find themselves on the Muppet Show
Some members of the National Assembly were shocked by the proposal to change their title to MWP (Member of the Welsh Parliament, representative of the Welsh Parliament).
The alarm arose after it was suggested that the name of the National Assembly (Assembly) should be the Parliament of Wales (Welsh Parliament).
Now representatives from different political backgrounds fear that the new title may make them laugh.
According to one Labour MP, his faction is concerned that their new name will rhyme with the words "Twp" and "Pwp".
For the sake of our non-Walesian readers: in Welsh, twp means simple-minded, and pwp means poop.
According to a representative of the Plaid party, the whole faction is "unsatisfied" and therefore alternatives are proposed.
One Conservative MP said his faction was "open" to name change, however he noted that the MWP was just a jump from "Muppet".
Here it is worth noting that in Welsh, the letter "w" is pronounced similar to the word "u" in Yorkshire English, or MWP pronounced "map".
The position of the National Assembly Committee responsible for drawing up the draft law introducing the name change is as follows: "The final decision on the titles for naming members of the National Assembly is, of course, in the hands of the Members."
The 2017 law governing the governance of Wales allowed the Welsh National Assembly to change its name.
In June, the Commission published the results of a public consultation proposing the inclusion of the name of the Welsh Parliament and which gained broad support.
With regard to the title of Members, the Commission prefers the Welsh Parliament Member (Representative of the Welsh Parliament) and its abbreviation WMP, but the public consultation favoured the MWP alternative.
Members come up with more and more alternatives, but the agreement is rather cumbersome, causing problems for the National Assembly President Elin Jones, who will have to submit the bill on name changes in the coming weeks.
The reform law will also affect the functioning of the National Assembly at other points, including the disqualification of Members and committee structures.
Members will be able to take their final vote on the matter of their own title during the debate on the draft law.
